(\Omega,\mathcal{A},\mu)
\sigma
 \mathcal{N}_{\mu}:=\left\{N\subset\Omega : \exists M\in\mathcal{A}, N\subset M, \mu(M)=0\right\} 
 (i)~\emptyset\in\mathcal{N}_{\mu},~~~~~(ii)~N\in\mathcal{N}_{\mu}, B\subset N\Rightarrow B\in\mathcal{N}_{\mu},~~~~~(iii)~(N_n)_n\in\mathcal{N}_{\mu}^{\mathbb{N}}\Rightarrow\bigcup_n N_n\in\mathcal{N}_{\mu} 
\emptyset\in\mathcal{A}, \mu(\emptyset)=0
\emptyset\subset\emptyset
\emptyset\in\mathcal{N}_{\mu}
N\in\mathcal{N}_{\mu}, B\subset N
M\in\mathcal{A}
N\subset M, \mu(M)=0
B\subset M, \mu(M)=0
B\in\mathcal{N}_{\mu}
(N_n)_n\in\mathcal{N}_{\mu}^{\mathbb{N}}
N_n,n\geq 1
M_n\in\mathcal{A}
N_n\subset M_n, \mu(M_n)=0
\sigma
\mu
\bigcup_{n\geq 1}N_n\in\mathcal{N}_{\mu}
 \bigcup_{n\geq 1}N_n\subset\bigcup_{n\geq 1}M_m 
 \mu(\bigcup_{n\geq 1}M_n)=\sum_{n\geq 1}\mu(M_n)=0. 
